ue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required (orders 1–6).\n- `accounts`, `account_contracts`, `contacts` (2), `activities` (6), `benchmark_fixture` (1): supporting context.\n- `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`: all **empty arrays** — these are what the workflow must populate.\n\nI confirmed `npm test` currently FAILS at line 19 (status assertion: `'Needs work'` vs the expected escalation string), matching `tests-before.log`. The npm wrapper masks the real exit code (reports 0), but the underlying assertion throws.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** This is a zero-dependency Node ESM benchmark target with no real Postgres — the \"DB\" is `data/tables.json` (normalized tables), and the only file to implement is `src/workflow.mjs`, which must persist `workflow_state` (1 row, with status + next_step), `owner_tasks` (one `{owner_group, title, due_at, status:\"open\"}` per owner group in group_order), one `customer_messages` row (with `body`), and one `audit_events` row (with `customer_visible` truthy) into the passed-in tables, then return `buildPortalView(db)` so the seven `after.*` assertions in the unchangeable `tests/acceptance.test.mjs` pass."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":566,"cache_read_input_tokens":29542,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":566},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Aw9RG3RKgWz65ESasyHMqA","session_id":"3f601996-8bd7-4ee8-8366-486834d75ed1","uuid":"3713e320-36d2-46d8-bb83-51da7a8838ff","subagent_type":"worker","task_description":"Explore workspace structure"}
