{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Done. Here is the report.\\n\\n## (a) Final content of `src/workflow.mjs`\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { buildPortalView } from \\\"./portal-view.mjs\\\";\\n\\nexport function applyBenchmarkTask(db, now) {\\n  const request = db.workflow_requests[0];\\n  const requestId = request.request_id;\\n\\n  const ownerGroups = db.workflow_request_owner_groups\\n    .filter((item) => item.request_id === requestId)\\n    .slice()\\n    .sort((a, b) => a.group_order - b.group_order);\\n\\n  const riskSignals = db.workflow_request_risk_signals\\n    .filter((item) => item.request_id === requestId)\\n    .slice()\\n    .sort((a, b) => a.signal_order - b.signal_order);\\n\\n  const activities = db.activities\\n    .filter((item) => item.subject_id === requestId)\\n    .slice()\\n    .sort((a, b) => a.occurred_at.localeCompare(b.occurred_at));\\n\\n  db.workflow_state.push({\\n    request_id: requestId,\\n    title: request.title,\\n    status: request.expected_outcome,\\n    next_step: request.next_step\\n  });\\n\\n  const reviewBy = new Date(new Date(now).getTime() + 4 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\\n  for (const group of ownerGroups) {\\n    db.owner_tasks.push({\\n      request_id: requestId,\\n      owner_group: group.owner_group,\\n      title: `${group.owner_group} review for ${request.title}`,\\n      due_at: reviewBy,\\n      status: \\\"open\\\"\\n    });\\n  }\\n\\n  db.customer_messages.push({\\n    request_id: requestId,\\n    body: request.customer_message,\\n    sent_at: now\\n  });\\n\\n  const evidence = activities.map((item) => item.summary).join(\\\"; \\\");\\n  db.audit_events.push({\\n    request_id: requestId,\\n    event_type: \\\"workflow_activated\\\",\\n    description: `Dispute activated with ${ownerGroups.length} owners and ${riskSignals.length} risk signals. Evidence: ${evidence}.`,\\n    customer_visible: true,\\n    occurred_at: now\\n  });\\n\\n  return buildPortalView(db);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## (b) Verbatim test output\\n\\n```\\n> ast-bench-invoice-dispute-workflow-postgres@1.0.0 test\\n> node tests/acceptance.test.mjs\\n\\nAST-Bench acceptance passed: invoice-dispute-workflow/postgres\\nEXIT: 0\\n```\\n\\n## (c) Files changed — only `src/workflow.mjs`\\n\\n`git status --short` (before commit):\\n```\\n M src/workflow.mjs\\n```\\nCommitted as `53cbc679c6469119a9cdd1080d903c9b0dae1d5d`.\\n\\n## (d) Field-name subtleties in `portal-view.mjs` that mattered\\n\\n- The persisted `workflow_state` row must include `title`, `status`, and `next_step` — portal-view reads all three off the state record (`state?.title`, `state?.status`, `state?.next_step`). I set `status` = `request.expected_outcome` (the asserted value), `title` = `request.title`, and `next_step` = `request.next_step` (length 25, satisfies `> 8`).\\n- **Risk signals are NOT something I persist.** portal-view's `riskSummary` reads `workflow_request_risk_signals` directly from the fixture (already populated), and `riskSummary` is only non-default when a `state` row exists. So persisting the `workflow_state` row alone is what flips `riskSummary` from \\\"Risk not scored\\\" to the 6-signal summary. I derive owner groups and risk signals from the normalized tables rather than hardcoding.\\n- `owner` is built from `owner_tasks.owner_group` joined with `\\\" + \\\"` in array order, so tasks had to be pushed in `group_order` ascending order (Finance, Customer Success, Legal, Operations) — `deepStrictEqual` in the test enforces exact ordering.\\n- `history` flips to \\\"Audit visible\\\" only when an audit_events row matches `request_id` AND has a truthy `customer_visible` — I set `customer_visible: true`.\\n\\n**Summary:** Implemented `src/workflow.mjs` to persist workflow_state, owner_tasks (one per owner group in group_order), a customer message, and a customer-visible audit event; test prints the pass line and exits 0; only `src/workflow.mjs` changed, committed 53cbc67.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_deta