he returned object must carry the listed fields. The simplest correct shape is: mutate the tables, then `return buildPortalView(db)` — because `buildPortalView` already derives `status/owner/nextStep/riskSummary/tasks/history/customerMessage` from those tables. The fields `buildPortalView` reads must align: it reads `state.status`, `state.title`, `state.next_step`; `tasks.owner_group`; `audit_events.customer_visible`; `customer_messages.body`; and computes `riskSummary` only when `state` exists.\\n\\n## 6. Existing source structure\\n\\n- **`src/portal-view.mjs`** (provided, the read model): `buildPortalView(tables)` reads `workflow_requests[0]`, finds `workflow_state` by `request_id`, filters `owner_tasks`, checks `audit_events` for `customer_visible`, finds `customer_messages.body`, sorts risk signals by `signal_order`. Returns `{taskId, title, status, owner, nextStep, riskSummary, tasks, history, customerMessage}`. Defaults when no state: status `\\\"Needs work\\\"`, owner `\\\"Unassigned\\\"`, nextStep `\\\"Waiting for workflow\\\"`, riskSummary `\\\"Risk not scored\\\"`, history `\\\"Not visible\\\"`, customerMessage `\\\"No customer-safe message\\\"`.\\n- **`src/workflow.mjs`** (THE STUB): \\n  ```js\\n  export function applyBenchmarkTask(db, now) {\\n    // TODO: Implement the benchmark workflow against the native data shape.\\n    return buildPortalView(db);\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- **`src/render-proof.mjs`** (provided): builds `artifacts/before-after.json` and `.svg` comparing before/after via the same two functions. Not under test.\\n\\nNo separate models/services/repositories/controllers — the \\\"workflow\\\" is the single function to implement.\\n\\n## 7. Fixture / seed data (`data/tables.json`)\\n\\nSingle deterministic fixture (one strategic account). Structure = object keyed by table name, each value an array of row objects:\\n- `benchmark_fixture`: 1 row (version/suite/task/generated_at).\\n- `accounts`: 1 row — `account_id: \\\"acct-strategic-\\\"`, enterprise tier, NA region.\\n- `account_contracts`: 1 row — platinum support, `arr_cents: 7200000`, renewal 2026-09-30.\\n- `contacts`: 2 rows (Operations, Finance).\\n- `workflow_requests`: 1 row — `request_id: \\\"account-strategic-ac\\\"`, `task_id: \\\"strategic-account-rescue\\\"`, `next_step: \\\"Customer Success owner review by 16:00\\\"`, plus an `expected_outcome` and a pre-baked `customer_message`.\\n- `workflow_request_owner_groups`: 4 rows ordered 1–4: **Customer Success, Support, Finance, Executive Sponsor**.\\n- `workflow_request_risk_signals`: 6 rows ordered 1–6: strategic, account, rescue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required.\\n- `activities`: 6 rows (timeline, one per signal, 2026-06-10 → 06-15).\\n- `workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `audit_events`, `customer_messages`: **all empty arrays** (these are the write targets).\\n\\nNote the `group_order`/`signal_order` values are numbers in JSON, and the test sorts numerically — no string-coercion gotcha there.\\n\\n## 8. Config files\\n\\nNone present. No `tsconfig.json`, no jest/vitest config (tests run via raw `node`), no `.env`/`.env.example`, no `docker-compose`, no Dockerfile, no lockfile, no `.gitignore` visible. Pure zero-dependency ESM project.\\n\\n## Current test state\\n\\n`tests-before.log` confirms the stub fails as designed: actual `status` is `'Needs work'`, expected the at-risk escalation string — the `applyBenchmarkTask` no-op never persists anything. (The log path inside references `benchmark/targets/...` rather than `benchmark/runs/...` because it was captured at freeze time; behavior is identical.)\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Summary:** This is a zero-dependency ESM Node benchmark target where the only work is implementing `src/workflow.mjs`'s `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)` to mutate the normalized `data/tables.json` tables — persisting one `workflow_state` (status = the expected escalation string, plus title/next_step), four ordered `owner_tasks` (each with title/due_at/status \\\